
[1]insult

   IN'SULT, n. [L. insultus, from insilio, to leap on; in and salio, to
   leap.]

   1. The act of leaping on. [Little used.]

   2. Any gross abuse offered to another, either by words or actions; act
   or speech of insolence or contempt.

   The ruthless sneer that insult adds to grief.
